Compilation of server and client files:
gcc server.c -o server.out
gcc client.c -o client.out 

Running server and client files. 

./client.out localhost 9999

Mode_error = 0  for server means that server will be working fine and will send response if packet is received.
Mode_error =1 for server will not send acknoledgment this is to validate timeout and retransmission

./server.out 9999 0
./server.out 9999 1

